<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
The earlier record of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus cognatus" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognatus">Haplodrassus cognatus</taxonomicName>
from Crimea was based on specimens of unknown sex and number from Karadag Nature Reserve (
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Bragina 1984</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus cognatus" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognatus">Haplodrassus cognatus</taxonomicName>
is absent in our material from Crimea, although we have large collections, especially from the Karadag Reserve). It is reasonable to conclude that the earlier records of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus cognatus" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognatus">Haplodrassus cognatus</taxonomicName>
from Crimea represent a misidentified material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
