<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus cognatus" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognatus">Haplodrassus cognatus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Haplodrassus</taxonomicName>
species by its straight terminal apophysis with a basal tooth in males, and by the shape of the fovea and wide anterior hood (Ah) in females.
</paragraph>
