<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
It has a trans-Palearctic boreo-nemoral range and occurs from France to Hokkaido, north to north Ural and Tomsk, and south to Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, YM" journalOrPublisher="IBPN FEB RAS, Magadan" pageId="13" pageNumber="72" title="Spiders of Tuva, South Siberia." year="2000">Marusik et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Helsdingen 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Platnick 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
